WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.792
So, last Thursday we had the confirmation
candidates here, and today we have the

00:00:07.792 --> 00:00:10.575
first communicants and their parents.

00:00:10.575 --> 00:00:18.924
We have young people and those who are
following via Laudato TV, and it's hard

00:00:18.924 --> 00:00:22.820
to make a sermon that includes everyone.

00:00:22.820 --> 00:00:25.047
Sun, are you ready?

00:00:25.047 --> 00:00:27.830
Who gave you the rosary?

00:00:30.654 --> 00:00:37.894
Church, but it's not a pastor. Great! Are
you excited about your first communion?

00:00:37.894 --> 00:00:40.480
Have you learned any songs?

00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:44.100
Some of you said yes, some no.

00:00:44.100 --> 00:00:50.306
Okay, those who said yes,
let me hear which song it is.

00:00:50.306 --> 00:00:55.995
Just the beginning, then start
singing, the group will support you.

00:00:57.210 --> 00:00:58.450
How does the song go?

00:01:15.530 --> 00:01:16.610
Bravo!

00:01:34.830 --> 00:01:36.750
Great, well done.

00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:50.794
Do you know, do you know, my dears,
what I am holding here in my hand?

00:01:50.794 --> 00:01:53.635
That's right, the Bible,
the Holy Scripture.

00:01:53.635 --> 00:01:57.693
And why did I bring the
Bible, the Holy Scripture?

00:01:57.693 --> 00:02:01.752
Because someone gave birth to
you, raised you, and prepared

00:02:01.752 --> 00:02:03.781
you for this holy communion.

00:02:03.781 --> 00:02:05.405
And who is that?

00:02:05.405 --> 00:02:06.623
Parents, that's right.

00:02:06.623 --> 00:02:13.523
And now, in this second part, we will talk
a bit about parents, because here God has

00:02:13.523 --> 00:02:16.769
written how they must take care of you.

00:02:16.769 --> 00:02:18.965
Or did you know that?

00:02:18.965 --> 00:02:25.113
Now listen to the sermon, and next
time they aren't good to you, tell

00:02:25.113 --> 00:02:30.822
them, hey, the Holy Scripture says,
God said to raise us this way.

00:02:30.822 --> 00:02:32.579
Did you remember that?

00:02:32.579 --> 00:02:34.774
I'll open a quote here.

00:02:37.495 --> 00:02:42.106
There are many schools, many
psychology and pedagogy experts who

00:02:42.106 --> 00:02:45.334
talk about how you should be raised.

00:02:46.175 --> 00:02:50.184
However, at one university,
they conducted a study.

00:02:50.184 --> 00:02:53.191
This university is well-known at Harvard.

00:02:53.191 --> 00:03:00.208
They took children like you and
followed them for years as they grew up.

00:03:00.208 --> 00:03:06.723
They wanted to see what they
would be like when they grew up.

00:03:06.723 --> 00:03:14.241
They invested a lot of money in this
study to see what these children became

00:03:14.241 --> 00:03:17.750
and what they were like as adults.

00:03:18.910 --> 00:03:27.257
And as the years went by, they tracked
their development just like your

00:03:27.257 --> 00:03:34.962
parents track yours, and when they
grew up, they were quite mature,

00:03:34.962 --> 00:03:37.531
responsible, diligent, and hardworking.

00:03:37.531 --> 00:03:43.952
But the study revealed one
interesting thing: to become like

00:03:43.952 --> 00:03:47.805
that, they all had similar parents.

00:03:50.565 --> 00:03:54.950
And they noticed through that
study what the parents of

00:03:54.950 --> 00:03:56.705
those children were applying.

00:03:57.205 --> 00:03:59.078
They applied two things.

00:03:59.078 --> 00:04:01.888
One is that they applied love.

00:04:01.888 --> 00:04:08.445
And the other is something you might
like a bit less, which is... Discipline.

00:04:08.445 --> 00:04:15.470
It's a word from the holy scripture, so
let's say a bit of order, discipline.

00:04:15.470 --> 00:04:22.495
When you see this, you have monitors
here who ensure you don't talk or turn

00:04:22.495 --> 00:04:29.051
around, that's called discipline when the
monitor says no, be quiet, or your other

00:04:29.051 --> 00:04:32.330
parents who are watching over you here.

00:04:32.810 --> 00:04:40.587
So, dear parents and children, remember,
in order for someone to grow up to be

00:04:40.587 --> 00:04:48.364
good people and good believers, like these
young students you see here in front of

00:04:48.364 --> 00:04:52.511
you and around you, two things are needed.

00:04:52.511 --> 00:04:54.067
Love and discipline.

00:04:54.067 --> 00:05:01.325
Dear parents, I believe it's not easy
for you to raise children, and there's

00:05:01.325 --> 00:05:04.955
no manual that will tell you everything.

00:05:05.210 --> 00:05:12.514
Nowhere did you go to school to learn how
to be parents and raise children, because

00:05:12.514 --> 00:05:15.710
you just find yourself in that situation.

00:05:15.710 --> 00:05:20.732
But if you want to avoid
mistakes, use these two things.

00:05:20.732 --> 00:05:23.471
Now, I'm still holding this Bible.

00:05:23.471 --> 00:05:26.210
Is everything just about being smart?

00:05:26.210 --> 00:05:26.667
No.

00:05:26.667 --> 00:05:29.406
Who among you can read well?

00:05:29.406 --> 00:05:32.145
Come on, you here close by.

00:05:32.145 --> 00:05:34.885
You'll read this out loud, see?

00:05:50.375 --> 00:05:54.925
With the promise that it may
go well with you and that you

00:05:54.925 --> 00:05:57.025
may live long on the earth.

00:05:57.025 --> 00:06:02.275
And you, fathers, do not provoke your
children to anger, but bring them up in

00:06:02.275 --> 00:06:06.825
the discipline and instruction of the
Lord, the duties of slaves and masters.

00:06:06.825 --> 00:06:11.025
So maybe not everyone heard it
well, but it was read nicely.

00:06:11.025 --> 00:06:14.875
The first part says that you
children should obey your parents.

00:06:14.875 --> 00:06:19.425
And if you listened to your parents,
we wouldn't have any problems, right?

00:06:19.425 --> 00:06:23.275
However, sometimes that freedom leads
us to stop listening, especially when

00:06:23.275 --> 00:06:28.175
we grow up and become a bit rebellious
towards our parents, thinking, "What can

00:06:28.175 --> 00:06:30.625
they tell me?" And there's the problem.

00:06:31.085 --> 00:06:36.488
However, we are interested in this
fourth verse here, so you can remember

00:06:36.488 --> 00:06:42.308
it at home, this was the Epistle to
the Ephesians, chapter six, verse four.

00:06:42.308 --> 00:06:47.711
It refers a bit more to fathers,
but mothers can apply it too.

00:06:47.711 --> 00:06:53.115
And it goes like this: And you
fathers, do not provoke your children

00:06:53.115 --> 00:06:58.935
to anger, but bring them up in the
discipline and instruction of the Lord.

00:06:59.435 --> 00:07:06.367
You see, we don't need universities and
surveys to know how to raise children.

00:07:06.367 --> 00:07:09.339
The Holy Scripture already tells us.

00:07:09.339 --> 00:07:15.281
However, in this sentence from
the fourth verse, did you hear it?

00:07:15.281 --> 00:07:18.748
The first thing parents must not do.

00:07:18.748 --> 00:07:20.233
Did you remember?

00:07:20.233 --> 00:07:24.195
It says fathers must not
embitter their children.

00:07:24.195 --> 00:07:32.118
Dear parents, one of the first things, and
it's true, is that there are parents who

00:07:32.118 --> 00:07:35.090
can make their children's lives bitter.

00:07:35.600 --> 00:07:39.462
There are parents who do not love.

00:07:39.462 --> 00:07:44.981
For whom being a parent
feels like a heavy burden.

00:07:44.981 --> 00:07:52.155
And if children do not experience love,
what the Holy Scripture talks about

00:07:52.155 --> 00:07:55.466
happens, bitterness grows in their hearts.

00:07:55.466 --> 00:08:00.985
Let's see in the Holy
Scripture how this comes about.

00:08:03.865 --> 00:08:08.124
In the Book of Genesis,
we have two brothers.

00:08:08.124 --> 00:08:12.384
Have you heard the story of Cain and Abel?

00:08:12.384 --> 00:08:19.957
They had the same upbringing, yet one son
had a deep reverence for God while the

00:08:19.957 --> 00:08:27.530
other was full of bitterness and anger, to
the point of wanting to kill his brother.

00:08:28.169 --> 00:08:29.399
Oh, that's right.

00:08:29.399 --> 00:08:35.135
But you see, you parents often apply the
same upbringing to all your children.

00:08:35.135 --> 00:08:40.052
But that doesn't guarantee that
all your children will be the same.

00:08:40.052 --> 00:08:45.788
You raise two, three, four kids the
same way, and they turn out different.

00:08:45.788 --> 00:08:48.657
We see this in the Holy Scriptures.

00:08:48.657 --> 00:08:51.525
Cain and Abel had the same upbringing.

00:08:51.525 --> 00:08:55.622
One wanted to kill his brother,
the other respected God.

00:08:55.622 --> 00:08:59.720
And you see, it shows how
important that love is.

00:08:59.720 --> 00:09:01.599
To avoid creating bitterness.

00:09:01.599 --> 00:09:04.417
And when do parents do that?

00:09:04.417 --> 00:09:09.115
Let's look at an example from
the Holy Scripture again.

00:09:09.115 --> 00:09:11.933
Why was Joseph sold into slavery?

00:09:11.933 --> 00:09:14.282
Have you heard that story?

00:09:14.282 --> 00:09:16.161
It's sad, isn't it?

00:09:16.161 --> 00:09:22.738
He had many brothers and sisters,
and in the end, he was sold, right?

00:09:22.738 --> 00:09:28.375
Tell me, sweetheart, say it into
the microphone so everyone can hear.

00:09:28.375 --> 00:09:33.542
Because he was the most
loved, he was the most loved.

00:09:33.542 --> 00:09:35.891
Was he perhaps the youngest?

00:09:35.891 --> 00:09:38.710
Yes, he was the youngest son.

00:09:40.150 --> 00:09:42.068
Who raised their hand?

00:09:42.068 --> 00:09:43.508
Tell us, Sokla.

00:09:43.508 --> 00:09:47.825
And why did his father love him the most?

00:09:47.825 --> 00:09:48.305
Bravo!

00:09:48.305 --> 00:09:54.061
When you parents create bitterness
in your children, when you choose a

00:09:54.061 --> 00:09:59.338
favorite child, his father, as the
youngest son... Especially loved him.

00:09:59.338 --> 00:10:03.176
He had the best suit made for him.

00:10:03.176 --> 00:10:09.892
He separated him from his other brothers
and sisters because he was his favorite.

00:10:09.892 --> 00:10:14.210
But what did that create
in the other children?

00:10:14.210 --> 00:10:18.135
What does the Holy Scripture
say about all this?

00:10:18.135 --> 00:10:18.571
Jealousy.

00:10:18.571 --> 00:10:19.008
Jealousy.

00:10:19.008 --> 00:10:19.880
Jealousy, anger.

00:10:19.880 --> 00:10:25.114
So you see, parents, how you can
make mistakes in raising children.

00:10:25.114 --> 00:10:28.604
When you don't love all
your children equally.

00:10:28.604 --> 00:10:34.274
And when you highlight one, praise
one, reward one, it's natural that it

00:10:34.274 --> 00:10:39.945
will create bitterness in the other, as
the Holy Scripture writes about here.

00:10:39.945 --> 00:10:43.435
And you fathers, do not
embitter your children.

00:10:43.715 --> 00:10:49.021
And that's why the brothers decided
to sell Joseph and express, let's

00:10:49.021 --> 00:10:53.886
say, their bitterness and anger
towards what their father had done.

00:10:53.886 --> 00:10:57.866
Many times, dear parents,
you need to be careful.

00:10:57.866 --> 00:11:04.942
I know some of you might think,
"What do you have to tell us? You are

00:11:04.942 --> 00:11:09.806
priests, you don't have children,"
but many times, this is exactly

00:11:09.806 --> 00:11:12.018
where bitterness forms in children.

00:11:12.018 --> 00:11:16.882
There are parents who, as the
Holy Scripture says, don't pay

00:11:16.882 --> 00:11:21.305
attention and can very easily make
their children's lives bitter.

00:11:21.484 --> 00:11:26.408
It doesn't always have to be
with a gesture or a material

00:11:26.408 --> 00:11:29.280
reward; it can also be with words.

00:11:29.280 --> 00:11:32.152
What do we hear the most today?

00:11:32.152 --> 00:11:35.024
We don't take these little suns seriously.

00:11:35.024 --> 00:11:37.485
So we think, they're just kids.

00:11:37.485 --> 00:11:39.537
Why should I praise them?

00:11:39.537 --> 00:11:45.691
If you want to make their lives bitter,
don't be present in their lives, don't

00:11:45.691 --> 00:11:51.025
have time for them, focus on other
things, don't be interested in how

00:11:51.025 --> 00:11:56.358
they're doing in school, how they're
doing in church, and you will create

00:11:56.358 --> 00:11:58.410
bitter individuals in the future.

00:11:58.590 --> 00:12:04.165
That's why the scripture keeps
repeating and telling us, fathers

00:12:04.165 --> 00:12:07.510
and mothers alike, to be careful.

00:12:07.510 --> 00:12:10.297
First, what shouldn't we do?

00:12:10.297 --> 00:12:13.085
We shouldn't embitter their lives.

00:12:13.085 --> 00:12:20.332
Second, a woman once told me, you
know how everyone wraps gifts for

00:12:20.332 --> 00:12:23.120
Christmas, related to this topic.

00:12:23.120 --> 00:12:30.925
One mother, who had four children,
would always put the price on each gift.

00:12:32.564 --> 00:12:37.683
Then one son asked, "Mom, why do
you always do that?" Because she

00:12:37.683 --> 00:12:40.439
knew the list of all the gifts.

00:12:40.439 --> 00:12:46.738
She said, "I don't want you to compete
among yourselves and say, 'I got a more

00:12:46.738 --> 00:12:53.431
expensive gift.' I want you all to see the
price, that you all got the same, because

00:12:53.431 --> 00:12:59.337
I love you all equally." So, mom and dad
should love all their children equally.

00:12:59.337 --> 00:13:05.243
And you see how much care and love this
mother had, that she even highlighted

00:13:05.243 --> 00:13:10.755
the price so that brother and sister or
brother and brother would never argue,

00:13:10.755 --> 00:13:15.480
not be resentful, and not fall into
temptation like Joseph's brothers did.

00:13:16.100 --> 00:13:20.342
Here, furthermore, this word
says... That one should raise with

00:13:20.342 --> 00:13:22.887
discipline and admonition of the Lord.

00:13:22.887 --> 00:13:26.705
What is the discipline and
admonition of the Lord?

00:13:30.695 --> 00:13:36.916
So, it means to tell parents
that God was an excellent parent.

00:13:36.916 --> 00:13:41.063
God led His chosen people
through the desert.

00:13:41.063 --> 00:13:45.729
He cared for them, an
excellent parent without flaw.

00:13:45.729 --> 00:13:49.358
Yet, they still didn't listen to Him.

00:13:49.358 --> 00:13:54.542
But that same Father forgave
every time, loved every time,

00:13:54.542 --> 00:14:00.245
showed tenderness every time, and
always waited for them to return.

00:14:00.645 --> 00:14:04.798
That's what it means to raise
children with God's grace.

00:14:04.798 --> 00:14:08.120
To be like God who forgives, who loves.

00:14:08.120 --> 00:14:12.689
It's sad, dear parents, if your
children never see your tears.

00:14:12.689 --> 00:14:16.011
If they don't see your concern for them.

00:14:16.011 --> 00:14:20.580
If they don't see your phone
calls, your worry, that's sad.

00:14:20.580 --> 00:14:26.395
We are afraid to show emotions, love,
and concern in front of our children.

00:14:26.395 --> 00:14:31.100
They will appreciate it more when
they see your tears and concern

00:14:31.100 --> 00:14:33.060
for them rather than coldness.

00:14:33.060 --> 00:14:38.157
The problem is that they memorize
everything now, but what are we creating,

00:14:38.157 --> 00:14:44.823
as that study suggests, what will they be
like in 5, 10, 20 years as grown adults?

00:14:44.823 --> 00:14:51.488
Will they be men who are not afraid to
cry and show emotions, or will they be

00:14:51.488 --> 00:14:57.370
icebergs who don't know how to deal with
their pain, while we all want change?

00:14:57.970 --> 00:15:02.983
So, that's why we talk about this
upbringing and discipline like God who

00:15:02.983 --> 00:15:04.912
raises us, because what's important?

00:15:04.912 --> 00:15:08.383
It's not just important to give
children everything material.

00:15:08.383 --> 00:15:14.168
That's why it is said here that we
need to care for their spiritual state.

00:15:14.168 --> 00:15:15.710
But listen to this.

00:15:15.710 --> 00:15:21.495
If you've read the Book of Genesis or
the beginnings of the Bible, when God

00:15:21.495 --> 00:15:26.895
addresses Moses and wants to tell him
what to do, like a parent teaching

00:15:26.895 --> 00:15:32.680
their people, He speaks to him about
His word, but first says this to Moses.

00:15:33.635 --> 00:15:39.855
Let my word first be engraved in
your heart, and then teach others.

00:15:39.855 --> 00:15:47.033
So parents, God's word, faith, must first
be engraved in your hearts to teach them.

00:15:47.033 --> 00:15:52.775
Because what they receive from their
family, they cannot get anywhere else.

00:15:52.775 --> 00:15:54.689
We cannot replace you.

00:15:54.689 --> 00:16:01.388
The church is here to assist, but
you are the ones who ultimately need

00:16:01.388 --> 00:16:07.130
to raise them with the discipline
of the Lord, and that's it.

00:16:07.470 --> 00:16:11.458
So, you have love for
God and to teach them.

00:16:11.458 --> 00:16:16.643
If they see the Bible in your
hands, they will surely read it.

00:16:16.643 --> 00:16:23.423
If they see you holding a mobile phone
all day, they will be on their phones too.

00:16:23.423 --> 00:16:27.412
Don't wait for changes from
the children, you change first.

00:16:27.412 --> 00:16:33.395
Because you will shape them into the
people they will be in five, ten years.

00:16:33.755 --> 00:16:37.423
That's why God's word is wonderful.

00:16:37.423 --> 00:16:39.869
And God is wonderful.

00:16:39.869 --> 00:16:41.704
Isn't that right?

00:16:41.704 --> 00:16:43.538
Is God good?

00:16:43.538 --> 00:16:48.430
And does He love all of us here?

00:16:48.430 --> 00:16:50.265
And Sister Ivanka?

00:16:54.305 --> 00:16:57.910
But do you love God?

00:16:57.910 --> 00:16:58.631
Great.

00:16:58.631 --> 00:17:02.236
Shall we pray together now?

00:17:02.236 --> 00:17:08.004
You don't have to respond
to every question.

00:17:18.155 --> 00:17:21.155
Now you will pray, but
do you know for whom?

00:17:26.230 --> 00:17:27.950
For whom should I pray now?

00:17:30.530 --> 00:17:33.594
Here, he got it right.

00:17:33.594 --> 00:17:35.433
For the parents.

00:17:35.433 --> 00:17:39.724
Do you know any prayers for parents?

00:17:39.724 --> 00:17:40.950
Not really.

00:17:43.780 --> 00:17:46.165
Alright, now we will do it.

00:17:46.165 --> 00:17:46.563
Okay?

00:17:46.563 --> 00:17:47.358
Calm down.

00:17:47.358 --> 00:17:51.733
Because when you pray for them,
they will change towards you.

00:17:51.733 --> 00:17:53.721
They will be even better.

00:17:53.721 --> 00:17:57.698
They are great now, but
they will be even better.

00:17:57.698 --> 00:17:58.493
Okay, dears?

00:17:58.493 --> 00:18:02.470
Now each of you pray for your mom and dad.

00:18:02.470 --> 00:18:02.935
Okay?

00:18:02.935 --> 00:18:06.189
Come on, close your eyes, calm down.

00:18:09.270 --> 00:18:15.007
Imagine a picture of your
mom and dad in front of you.

00:18:15.007 --> 00:18:18.833
Don't look at me, just close your eyes.

00:18:18.833 --> 00:18:20.745
And repeat after me.

00:18:20.745 --> 00:18:27.440
Dear God, thank you for the lives
of my mom and dad, thank you.

00:18:30.550 --> 00:18:33.450
thank you for taking care of me

00:18:36.360 --> 00:18:40.500
you who quickly forgive me
when I make a mistake, please

00:18:44.240 --> 00:18:46.360
grant them the spirit of patience

00:18:51.125 --> 00:19:02.235
Spirit of love, so they selflessly give to
us, and that we become the best we can be.

00:19:05.655 --> 00:19:16.595
Bless me, my mom, dad, brother, sister,
and everyone who takes care of me.

00:19:19.805 --> 00:19:26.383
Help me, Jesus, to be the best I can.

00:19:26.383 --> 00:19:27.114
Amen.

00:19:27.114 --> 00:19:29.306
Was it hard?

00:19:29.306 --> 00:19:34.423
See, you can do this every day.

00:19:34.423 --> 00:19:35.885
Say it.

00:19:45.205 --> 00:19:48.665
Did you ask mom and dad
if you might have one?

00:19:51.725 --> 00:19:53.945
I'm joking, I'm joking.

00:19:57.185 --> 00:19:58.345
Had enough?

00:20:07.005 --> 00:20:13.362
But what, let me just ask you, did
you notice these young people here?

00:20:13.362 --> 00:20:13.816
Yes.

00:20:13.816 --> 00:20:16.541
What would you say to them?

00:20:16.541 --> 00:20:19.720
You can do it, you will succeed.

00:20:36.810 --> 00:20:39.290
After this, I can only say amen.

